    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-01-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <head>13. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> to
                    Egyptian President <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d13fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> Office Files, Box 133, Country Files, Middle East,
                        Egypt, Volume 10, February 1974. Secret. According to <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>’s memoirs, <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> drafted the letter himself. (<hi
                            rend="italic">Years of Upheaval</hi>, pp. 834–835)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1974-01-17">January 17, 1974</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Mr. President:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I understand that once the agreement between Egypt and Israel on disengagement of
                    forces is in effect, you intend to begin work looking toward an early return of
                    the Suez Canal to full operation and toward the rehabilitation of the cities and
                    towns along the Canal and the resumption of normal economic activities in that
                    area. I want you to know that if you proceed in this way the United States gives
                    you its assurance that Israel will refrain from taking any military action
                    against those civilian centers, installations and populations.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_NRM_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Richard Nixon</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
